                <h1>Easy Tips for Removing Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>To effectively remove wallpaper, start by scoring the surface with a wallpaper scraper to create small holes. Next, apply a wallpaper removal solution or a mix of water and vinegar to saturate the paper. Allow it to soak for 15-20 minutes. Gently peel the wallpaper away from the wall. For stubborn sections, repeat the soaking process.</p>
